article.headline: Bowling Green 70, Toledo 69
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Germain Fitch scored on a layup with 27 seconds left and Bowling Green overcame a 17-point halftime deficit to hold off Toledo 70-69 on Saturday night. John Reimold had 17 points, John Floyd 13, Fitch 12 and Josh Almanson 10 for the Falcons (11-4, 5-2 Mid-American Conference. Keith Triplett led Toledo (7-8, 3-3) with 26 points. The Rockets led 34-17 at the half only to go scoreless for the first 3:10 of the second half. Bowling Green ran off nine points in a row over that span. The game was tied five times before the teams traded the lead four times in a 60-second span. Toledo's last lead came on Triplett's jumper with 39 seconds left. The Falcons came back and scored when Floyd assisted on Fitch's layup. Toledo set up for a final shot, but Justin Ingram's 3-pointer was off the mark, with Floyd rebounding to seal the win. The Falcons hit 76 percent of their shots in the second half (19 of 25) to offset 30-percent shooting and 17 turnovers in the first half. They had just four turnovers in the second half.
